<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSURANCE BILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Assemblyman Patrick Johnston's (D-Stockton) low-cost, no-frills, auto insurance 
bill for inner-city residents was killed (Part A, Jan. 18). 
</P>
<P>
Pity the person who is a victim of high grocery prices, an emergency trauma 
network with gaping holes and crime. Add to that some trial lawyers and 
politicians who are ostensibly their champions, but instead turn their backs on 
these poor folks at the call of self-interest. 
</P>
<P>
We can only hope for a miracle. Maybe the impoverished will become informed, 
will communicate and their anger will not lapse into apathy, but will be 
channeled in such a way to challenge those responsible for this unfortunate 
development. 
</P>
<P>
D. MICHAEL BUSH 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
