<HEADLINE>
<P>
CIVIL RIGHTS DAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With the apparent increased racial divisiveness triggered by the establishment 
of the Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. holiday, perhaps we should substitute a 
celebration of an underlying integrating concept, instead of resorting to the 
traditional practice of exalting personalities over ideas. 
</P>
<P>
My nomination is to re-designate the King holiday as Civil Rights Day, a 
concept deserving of universal support. In this way an opportunity would be 
provided to honor all those who contributed to the advancement of civil rights, 
including Dr. King. 
</P>
<P>
GEORGE V. HALL 
</P>
<P>
Torrance 
</P>
</TEXT>
