<HEADLINE>
<P>
JUST CAUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The Old Gringo," Carlos Fuentes' book about the terminal period in the life of 
Ambrose Bierce, a journalist for William Randolph Hearst some 80 years ago, 
contains a passage which is shocking in the similarity to President Bush's 
statement on the rationale for Operation Just Cause in Panama: 
</P>
<P>
"I did it to save lives." Bierce is reflecting on Mexico: "This land . . . He 
(Bierce) had never seen it before; he had attacked it by orders of his boss 
Hearst, who had enormous investments in ranches and other property and feared 
the Revolution; but he couldn't say, Go protect my property, he had to say, Go 
protect our lives, there are North American citizens in danger, intervene!" 
</P>
<P>
PAUL MORANDA 
</P>
<P>
Orange 
</P>
</TEXT>
