<HEADLINE>
<P>
FESTIVAL TO MARK CHINESE NEW YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Miss Chinatown, Dale Wong, will highlight the second annual Chinese Lunar New 
Year Festival from noon to 4 p.m. Sunday at the Golden Cove Center in Rancho 
Palos Verdes. The center is at Hawthorne Boulevard and Palos Verdes Drive West. 
</P>
<P>
Celebrants will welcome the Year of the Horse, with the traditional Lion Dance, 
Chinese fortunetelling, martial arts and a sword dance. The Lion Dance is 
performed as a harbinger of good luck for the new year. 
</P>
<P>
The Year of the Horse is described by cultural consultant Angi Ma Wong as "a 
year of adventure, action, moving ahead, recklessness and whimsy." 
</P>
<P>
Jointly sponsored by Rancho Palos Verdes and the Golden Cove Center Assn., the 
free event will also include food booths, artists and their work, dancing and 
music. 
</P>
