<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: CHULA VISTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police chased two 16-year-old boys in a stolen car Wednesday morning for more 
than half an hour through Chula Vista and National City, ending with their 
arrests in Paradise Hills, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The boys did not halt for a routine traffic stop by a Chula Vista police 
officer about 8:15 a.m. on Palomar Street, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The officer followed the pair onto northbound Interstate 5, where they exited 
on 24th Street and National City police took over the pursuit. 
</P>
<P>
"The chase in National City went on for 32 minutes, and I couldn't begin to 
tell you where they all went," said a National City police spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
The car finally stopped at 9:20 a.m. at Morningside and Ablemarle streets in 
Paradise Hills. The boys got out and ran, but were caught by police. 
</P>
<P>
There were no injuries and no damage, police said. The two youths were being 
held on suspicion of auto theft, possession of stolen property and felony 
evading. 
</P>
