net loss of $102 million, contrasted with a profit of $23 million for the 1988 
period. The Arlington, Va., firm attributed the results to higher fuel costs, 
to recurring and one-time cost increases relating to its merger with Pacific 
Southwest Airlines and Piedmont Airlines and to Hurricane Hugo and the Bay Area 
Quake, which caused major disruptions of service. 
