<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cipher Data Products: The San Diego-based manufacturer of computer tape drives, 
a kind of backup data storage device, reported a loss of $12 million on sales 
of $41.5 million for the second quarter ended Dec. 31, contrasted with a $3.2 
million profit on sales of $53.8 million for the similar quarter a year ago. 
Cipher Data had previously announced that it expected to report losses of this 
magnitude. For the fiscal year to date, Cipher's losses stand at $26.1 million 
on revenue of $82.8 million, contrasted with a $7-million profit on sales of 
$105.9 million for the same six months the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
