</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A one-year building moratorium on Valley Boulevard has been extended again, 
allowing the city to halt new construction along the commercial strip until 
January, 1991. 
</P>
<P>
The extension would give city planners and a Valley Boulevard steering 
committee time to complete a specific plan, which will detail what percentage 
of an area should be devoted to certain uses and what types of projects -- 
hotels, restaurants, apartments -- the city wants developed. 
</P>
