<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: TEMPLE CITY; 
</P>
<P>
CITY MANAGER TO RETIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City Manager Karl Koski has announced he will retire June 30 from a public 
service career that spans three decades. 
</P>
<P>
Koski, 59, joined the city staff as an administrative assistant in 1961, a year 
after incorporation. He said he decided to retire to spend time with his 
family, travel and enjoy the outdoors. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council probably will begin with an in-house search for a new city 
manager, Koski said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
