<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
TASK FORCE MEMBER NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Guillermina Byrne, an attorney and former city planning commissioner, was 
appointed Tuesday by the Board of Directors to the city's Growth Management 
Task Force. She joins 12 others appointed last week to the 13-member task 
force, which, in cooperation with city planning staff members, will devise 
guidelines for Phase III of the city's growth management initiative. 
</P>
<P>
Those guidelines are expected to be completed in April for approval by the City 
Planning Commission and the Board of Directors. 
</P>
<P>
The initiative, passed by voters last March, will limit construction to 250 
residential units a year over the next 10 years. In addition, the initiative 
says that the combined annual footage of commercial projects larger than 25,000 
square feet may not exceed 250,000 square feet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
