<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Karl Dorrell, who helped lead Helix High School to the 1980 San Diego Section 
3-A championship, has been named an assistant coach at Northern Arizona. 
Dorrell also played at UCLA and for the Dallas Cowboys in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
Dorrell, whose responsibilities will be assigned later, is the eighth assistant 
named by Steve Axman, who was hired Dec. 1. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
MEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
UC San Diego broke into the NCAA Division III top 20 for the first time. The 
Tritons (14-4) are ranked No. 19. 
</P>
<P>
Claremont-Mudd, ranked No. 15, is the only other California team ranked in 
Division III. UCSD defeated Claremont-Mudd by 14 points earlier this season. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
MEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
Jose Luis Noriega, a sophomore at the University of San Diego, won the 72nd 
Annual Peruvian Open National Tennis title with a 7-6, 7-6, 6-1 victory over 
Sergio Cortes of Chile Sunday. Noriega, 20, is ranked No. 2 in the nation among 
NCAA Division I players, and the Toreros are ranked No. 17 as a team. 
</P>
<P>
USD opens its season at home with a match Friday at 1 p.m. against UC 
Riverside. 
</P>
<P>
Unseeded Cynthia MacGregor, a former No. 1 player at San Diego State, and 
sister Cammy lost to top-seeded Jana Novotna and Helena Sukova of 
Czechoslovakia, 7-5, 6-2 in the quarterfinals of the women's doubles at the 
Australian Open. 
</P>
</TEXT>
