<P>
Seidman Warns Panel: L. William Seidman, chairman of the Federal Deposit 
Insurance Corp. and of the Resolution Trust Corp., warned the House Banking 
Committee that President Bush's $50-billion savings and loan bailout likely 
will fall short but assured members of Congress that the crunch probably 
wouldn't come until after this year's election. Panel members reacted with 
