World Bank to Provide Mexico With $2 Billion: World Bank President Barber B. 
Conable Jr., said in a speech delivered in Mexico City on Latin American 
economic growth and reforms that the international agency will provide $2 
billion to support the reduction of Mexico's public foreign debt with 
commercial banks. The Mexican government and a 15-member Bank Advisory 
