<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Dodger star Steve Garvey, plagued by low ratings as a radio talk-show 
host in San Diego, was fired by station XTRA after six months. 
</P>
<P>
Garvey, 41, who finished his baseball career with the Padres, was told of his 
dismissal after completing his four-hour drive-time show at 9 a.m., according 
to station employees. 
</P>
<P>
Tom Jimenez, vice president and general manager of XTRA, said the station and 
Garvey had reached a settlement to cover the rest of his contract. Jimenez 
declined to reveal the settlement terms and the length of the original 
contract. 
</P>
<P>
"Steve's attitude was totally professional," Jimenez said. "He understands what 
we're doing here. We're good friends. He was a tremendous help and a pleasure 
to work with. He's a true Hall of Famer in my eyes. He's one of my heroes." 
</P>
