<P>
SEA VIEW LEAGUE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ESTANCIA WINS WITH 20-4 RUN IN 4TH QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN BECK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Trailing by 10 points entering the fourth quarter, Estancia High School rallied 
to defeat Corona del Mar, 55-49, in a Sea View League boys' basketball game 
Wednesday night at Corona del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
Augustin Heredia and Matt Fuerbringer each had eight points as the Eagles 
outscored the Sea Kings, 20-4, in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
The turnaround came after Corona del Mar's 11-2 run to end the third quarter. 
Estancia's Paul McDaniel fouled Mark Flint and then was called for a technical 
in the final seconds of the quarter. After Flint made three of four free throws 
the Sea Kings led, 45-35. 
</P>
<P>
But Estancia (12-7 overall, 3-2 in the league) went on a run of its own, 
outscoring Corona del Mar, 13-2, to take a 48-47 lead with about two minutes 
remaining. CdM is 13-6, 4-1. 
</P>
<P>
Heredia, the county leader in free throw percentage at 91%, finished with 11 of 
15 free throws and had a game-high 23 points. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff Jackson scored 17 for Corona del Mar but was limited to one free throw in 
the fourth quarter. MARTIN BECK 
</P>
</TEXT>
