<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEMOGLOBIN COUNT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DR. NEIL SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Question: Please explain what is meant by the "hemoglobin count." All I know is 
that it has something to do with the blood. 
</P>
<P>
Answer: The hemoglobin count is an indication of the amount of the substance in 
red blood cells that carries oxygen. 
</P>
<P>
For Terry, Concord, N.H.: A persistent cough may be the only complaint in an 
older person with asthma. 
</P>
</TEXT>
