<P>
HOUSE CALL: It happened Tuesday night on TV's "thirty-something." . . . The 
episode was about a woman who has ovarian cancer. 
</P>
<P>
Her husband knew just where to look for expertise -- even if he needed two 
tries to get the expert's name right. . . . On the phone to several bookstores 
he asked for a study by Dr. Philip DiSaia of the UCI Medical Center, co-author 
of the standard work on the subject. . . . "I get many different pronunciations 
of his name," says DiSaia's secretary Jan Everett. For the record, it's 
pronounced "de SIGH ah." Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
