</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two recently completed recycling projects diverted about 90 tons of potential 
refuse from overloaded dumps. 
</P>
<P>
In Irvine, Dewey's Rubbish Service collected and shredded more than 75 tons of 
Christmas trees. The mulch will be used by the city's landscaping departments. 
</P>
<P>
In Costa Mesa's first annual Telephone Book Recycling Program, sponsored by the 
city, the Costa Mesa Sanitary District and Orange Coast College Recycling 
Center, 15 tons of directories were collected for recycling. 
</P>
