<HEADLINE>
<P>
STENSTROM PLANS TO ATTEND STANFORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS FOSTER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
El Toro High School quarterback Steve Stenstrom has made an oral commitment to 
play football at Stanford University, according to his father, Pete Stenstrom. 
</P>
<P>
Stenstrom passed for 4,604 yards during his two-year career with the Chargers. 
Last season, he completed 178 of 270 for 2,830 yards and 25 touchdowns in 
leading El Toro to the Southern Section Division III championship game. 
</P>
<P>
The Chargers lost to Paramount, 26-20, in the title game. 
</P>
<P>
Stenstrom was named to the All-Orange County first team last season. 
</P>
<P>
Besides Stanford, Stenstrom also visited the University of Iowa. He had 
scheduled trips to Oregon and Princeton, but canceled them after visiting 
Stanford. CHRIS FOSTER 
</P>
</TEXT>
