<TEXT>
<P>
The brunch held on Jan. 21 at the home of Hon and Celia Turner in Newport Beach 
raised an estimated $1,500 for the Alternative Repertory Theater. 
</P>
<P>
Celia Turner was the chairwoman. 
</P>
<P>
The Tribute Dinner honoring Edward Olmos on Jan. 21 at the Westin South Coast 
Plaza in Costa Mesa raised an estimated $175,000 for the Simon Wiesenthal 
Center. Maurice Lewitt was chairman; Dr. Sheldon Zinbert and Dr. Galal Gough 
were co-chairmen. 
</P>
<P>
The Tribute Luncheon honoring Ygal Sonenshine on Jan. 21 at the Big Canyon 
Country Club raised an estimated $50,000 for the Hebrew University in 
Jerusalem. The event was organized by the Orange County chapter of the American 
Friends of the Hebrew University. 
