CHINA MODEL IN HONG KONG MIGHT BE SEEKING ASYLUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HONG KONG 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One of China's top fashion models has been reported missing from a Hong Kong 
hotel, fueling speculation she is seeking political asylum in the British 
colony, a Hong Kong newspaper said today. 
</P>
<P>
The Chinese-language Sing Tao Wen Pao said Zhu Bei, 22, disappeared with all 
her luggage from her hotel room just before she was due to return to China on 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The evening paper said Zhu had been seen around town on the arm of a prominent 
Hong Kong television actor during her nine-day visit to the colony to take part 
in a fashion promotion. 
</P>
<P>
It said rumors were circulating that Zhu, who came here with 12 other models 
from China, had defected. 
</P>
<P>
"We have no information about the reports and we do not comment on individual 
applications for asylum," a government spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Sino-Hong Kong relations are only just recovering from a furor caused when Hong 
Kong allowed a Chinese swimmer, Yang Yang, to leave the colony for the United 
States last October. 
</P>
<P>
Yang claimed asylum in Hong Kong on the grounds he had played a part in the 
pro-democracy movement that rocked China in May and June and that he faced 
punishment if he returned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
