<P>
LOS ALAMITOS; 
</P>
<P>
ALL STAR RACE FOR DON MACBETH FUND ANNOUNCES POST POSITIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Post positions have been drawn for Friday's First Annual All Star Jockeys Race, 
a harness racing exhibition featuring eight jockeys from Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
Four jockeys each will compete in two one-mile elimination races at 7:50 p.m. 
and 8:20 p.m. (after the second and third races) with the top two in each 
division returning for the championship at 9:15 p.m. (after the sixth race). 
</P>
<P>
This special exhibition will benefit the Don MacBeth Memorial Jockey Fund. 
</P>
<P>
Post positions in the first elimination are: 1. Laffit Pincay Jr.; 2. Gary 
Stevens; 3. Corey Black; 4. Alex Solis. 
</P>
<P>
From the rail out in the second elimination are: 1. Chris McCarron; 2. Eddie 
Delahoussaye; 3. Robbie Davis; 4. Ray Sibille. 
</P>
<P>
A list of pacers entered in the exhibition was not immediately available. 
</P>
<P>
Tim Conway, noted comedian and avid supporter of racing, will serve as Master 
of Ceremonies for the All Star Jockeys Race. 
</P>
<P>
Conway is co-founder of the Don MacBeth Fund, which was created to aid jockeys 
permanently or temporarily disabled. 
</P>
<P>
Lloyd Arnold, president and general manager of Los Alamitos, will make a 
$10,000 contribution to the fund on behalf of the track. 
</P>
